stimulus:
Part 1/3

Welcome to our study! Before starting the face perception task, it is important for us to understand our participants characteristics, so that our conclusions are scientifically valid.

Let's start with some questions about yourself.

Part 2/3

Thank you! We will continue with a series of questionnaires about your personality. Again, it is important that you answer truthfully. Please read the statements carefully and answer according to what describe you the best.
Please wait for the experiment to load...

Part 3/3

In the last part of the experiment, images of faces will be flashed on the screen.

These images were created specially for this experiment: about half of them are photos of real people, and the other half of faces were entirely computer-generated using a new AI algorithm that we want to test.

This algorithm, based on a new generation of deep-learning models, is able to produce photo-realistic images of faces according to pre-specified parameters (e.g., gender, age, emotion, ...).

Among the artificial faces generated, only those that best matched the characteristics of the real photos were selected for this experiment (same background, lighting conditions, age range, etc.).

In order to help us validate our algorithm, we will ask you to tell whether you think the faces you see are real (photos of real people) or fake (computer-generated).

After each image, you will be asked a series of questions, such as:

  • Whether you think the face you saw was real or fake.

  • How attractive you would find someone who looks like that.

  • How approachable (friendly and easy to talk to) you would find someone who looks like that.

  • How much you would trust someone who looks like that.

  • How much that face reminds you of someone you know.

  • How much you think it resembles yourself.

Below is an example of the questions you will be asked after each image:


We are interested in your first impressions. Please respond according to your gut feelings.
